blog.title: And here is where things get crazy

summary: OK THAT'S JUST NOT FAIR In an unbelievable alignment of the stars and fate, in an impossible coincidence of unprecedented...
body:
OK THAT’S JUST NOT FAIR

In an unbelievable alignment of the stars and fate, in an impossible coincidence of unprecedented timing, I finished listening to Critical Role the day Disturbed’s new album came out.

Do you know what song is on that album?! This little song called “Hold On to Memories.” No clue what this song even sounds like, no clue what to expect, so I play it.

I swear to god this was the fucking hardest I have cried in years.

This song, this fucking song that just god damn sucker punched me in the gut, god, there could not be a more perfect song to encapsulate saying good bye. I can’t listen to this song without crying. It’s just … It’s too perfect. Please listen to this song, it’s just … wonderful.

“Now go do the best things in life.

Take a bite of this world while you can.

Make the most of the rest of your life.

Make a ride of this world while you can.

Hold on to memories. Hold on to every moment. Keep them alive.

The world’s greatest tragedy is souls who are not remembered cannot survive.”

summary: It just hit me that the people who haven’t watched last night’s episode yet are probably so confused why everyone is flipping...
body:
It just hit me that the people who haven’t watched last night’s episode yet are probably so confused why everyone is flipping the fuck out about fluffernutters. 

People who haven’t watched last night’s episode might not know that this was the name of a plan Nott and Jester came up with to toss a keg of black powder into an underground room containing load bearing pillars and then shoot an explosive arrow at it.

And that Nott decided the best time to do this was right when Beau was in the thick of things.
